==English==
===Etymology===
[[black]] + [[Friday]]. The word '''black''' in the name refers standard accounting practice of using black ink to denote net profits, and red ink to denote net losses.

===Proper noun===
'''Black Friday''' ''(plural:'' '''[[Black Fridays]]''')
# A [[Friday]] darkened by [[catastrophe]].
#* See a ''[[w:Black Friday|list of notable Black Fridays]]'' at Wikipedia.
# ''(US)'' The day after [[Thanksgiving Day]], generally regarded as the first day of the Christmas season, and the busiest shopping day of the year.